==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*unþa-'', from Indo-European ''*ane-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[omma]], Old Norse [[ǫnd]], [[andi]] (Swedish [[ande]])

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[άνεμος]], Latin [[animus]], Old Irish [[anál]] (Welsh [[anadl]], Breton [[holan]]), Slavic ''*(v)onia'' (Russian [[вонь]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'oɹoθ/

===Noun===
'''oroþ''' ''n''
# [[breath]]

